The paper discusses a modeling framework for understanding the emergence and evolution of hierarchical structure in complex systems, which is a topic that can be applied to various fields within computer science. The use of symbols and sequences suggests a focus on natural language processing and machine learning, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.SI and cs.AI. The discussion of optimization and selection also suggests a focus on systems and control, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SY. The use of computation modeling suggests a focus on algorithms and data structures, which falls under the sub-category of cs.DS. Finally, the analysis of differences between incrementally designed hierarchies and clean-slate hierarchies suggests a focus on machine learning and optimization, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG.
